===Adjective===
{{en-adj-more}}

# Tending to [[resist]] [[change]].
#: ''The curriculum committee at this university is extremely '''conservative'''.''
# Based on [[pessimistic]] [[assumption]]s.
#: ''At a '''conservative''' estimate, growth may even be negative next year.''
# {{cattag|US|economics|politics|social sciences}} Supporting some [[combination]] of [[fiscal]], [[political]] or [[social]] conservatism.
# {{cattag|US|politics}} Relating to the [[Republican party]], regardless of its conservatism.
# {{cattag|UK|politics}} Relating to the [[Conservative party]].
# {{cattag|physics}} {{notcomp}} Neither creating nor destroying a given quantity.

